Kayode Oyero President of the United States, Donald Trump, Tuesday, showed sympathy for the Australian government over the bushfires that have wreaked devastating havoc in parts of the country. READ ALSO: Iran offers $80m bounty for Trump’s head Trump, who spoke on the telephone with the Prime Minister of Australia, Scott Morrison, to express the support of the American people, tweeted in response to Morrison’s tweet, “We love Australia!” Morrison had tweeted, “Thanks for the call Donald Trump and for your strong messages of sympathy, support and friendship for Australia during our terrible bushfire season. Thanks also to the American people for their many messages of support. Australia and the US are great mates.” See tweets: The PUNCH reports that millions of animals were feared dead in bushfires that wreaked havoc in east and south Australia. Thousands of people have also been relocated due to the bushfires.